sentences: Cheb i Sabbah (7 August 1947 – 6 November 2013) was a DJ and composer/producer known for combining Asian, Arabian, and African sounds into his compositions.
When he was a teenager, Sabbah moved to Paris and, in 1964, began his career DJing American soul music records.
In 1984, he settled as a DJ in San Francisco.
In 1989 he began using the stage name "Cheb i Sabbah", which translates to "young of the morning".
In 1989 he began using the stage name "Cheb i Sabbah", which translates to "young of the morning".
He was nominated for the BBC's 2006 Award for World Music in the Club Global category.
Sabbah was diagnosed with stage 4 stomach cancer in May 2011.
He died on November 6, 2013 in San Francisco.
